{
  "texts": [
    "The result of the operation is an activation map M. Figure 1 shows the convolution for an input time series and kernel ω = [-1, 0, 1].",
    "The first entry of the activation map M is the result of a dot-product between A 1:3 * ω = A 1:3 • ω = 0 + 0 + 3 = 3.",
    "Each convolution creates a series to series transform from time series to activation map.",
    "Activation maps are used to create summary features.",
    "The dilation technique is a method that enables a filter, such as a sliding window or kernel, to cover a larger portion of the time series data by creating empty spaces between the entries in the filter."
  ]
}